<dl id="n12135g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12135g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12135g"> 135(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ arrears of love</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Others fall still more into <mark>arrears of development</mark> and are recognised ultimately as imbecile. &sect; III. In asylums for imbeciles and idiots we meet with boys and girls, aged between seven and fourteen, who &mdash; classical Mongolian imbeciles in the sense of Dr. Langdon-Down &mdash; represent the Asylum type of Mongol. Some of these, indeed many, die before puberty. <small> F.G. Crookshank, <a name="MIOM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MIOM"><cite title="source">The Mongol in Our Midst</cite></a> (1924) 16</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
